CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 10, 1953, pg. 12 reads: "The Debutantes' Fathers...Here are the proud fathers, or relatives, of the Debutantes of 1953, who escorted the pretty girls to their positions in the gala Cotillion."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eighteen debutante fathers wearing tuxedos and light colored bow ties, including six seated on sofa, posed in Syria Mosque for 1953 Alpha Kappa Alpha cotillion
